  "body": "### Component\r\n\r\nForge\r\n\r\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\r\n\r\n- [X] Foundry\r\n- [X] Foundryup\r\n\r\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\r\n\r\n`forge 0.2.0 (3497cdc 2022-05-08T00:03:38.445221977+00:00)`\r\n\r\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\r\n\r\n`forge install foundry-rs/forge-std@ea7c38a`\r\n\r\n### Operating System\r\n\r\nLinux\r\n\r\n### Describe the bug\r\n\r\nOutput:\r\n```\r\nInstalling forge-std in \"/home/aye/Repos/test2/lib/forge-std\" (url: Some(\"https://github.com/foundry-rs/forge-std\"), tag: Some(\"ea7c38a\"))\r\nError:\r\n   0: tag/branch/commit \"ea7c38a\" does not exists\r\n\r\nLocation:\r\n   cli/src/cmd/forge/install.rs:114\r\n\r\nBacktrace omitted. Run with RUST_BACKTRACE=1 environment variable to display it.\r\nRun with RUST_BACKTRACE=full to include source snippets.\r\n```\r\n\r\nI believe the cause is that `check_tag` uses `git ls-remote` to check tags, which doesn't list full commit hash list.\r\nhttps://github.com/foundry-rs/foundry/blob/8cbcb7b381fc8338839f6afb7e6c82364755290a/cli/src/cmd/forge/install.rs#L106-L118\r\n",
